        <headline>Flood Advisory issued June 6 at 3:10PM EDT until June 6 at 5:15PM EDT by NWS Albany NY</headline>
        <description>* WHAT...Urban and small stream flooding caused by excessive
rainfall is expected.

* WHERE...Portions of east central and eastern New York, including
the following counties, in east central New York, Saratoga and
Schenectady. In eastern New York, Montgomery.

* WHEN...Until 515 PM EDT.

* IMPACTS...Minor flooding in low-lying and poor drainage areas.

* ADDITIONAL DETAILS...
- At 310 PM EDT, Doppler radar indicated heavy rain due to
thunderstorms. This will cause urban and small stream
flooding. Up to 0.5 inches of rain have fallen.
- Additional rainfall amounts up to 1 inch are expected over
the area. This additional rain will result in minor flooding.
- Some locations that will experience flooding include...
Schenectady, Rotterdam, Amsterdam, Scotia, Glenville,
Niskayuna, Duanesburg, Ballston Spa, Hagaman, Fort Johnson,
Galway, Rotterdam Junction, Pattersonville-Rotterdam
Junction, East Glenville, Alplaus, Burnt Hills, Charlton,
Princetown, Duane and Rectors.
- http://www.weather.gov/safety/flood
</description>
        <instruction>Turn around, don't drown when encountering flooded roads. Most flood
deaths occur in vehicles.</instruction>
